The Labour leader said Britain could have a better future out of the bloc if it slashes red tape and diverges from Brussels' regulations. But Sir Keir's comments sparked a furious reaction from the SNP's Westminster leader. Mr Blackford raged on Twitter: "This was the kind of lies we had from the extreme Brexiteers in the Vote Leave campaign. "It was nonsense then, it is nonsense now. "To see Labour adopting an extreme Brexit position when Brexit is making our cost of living crisis worse than Europe beggars belief." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES ON BREXIT: